WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.571 --> 00:00:05.205
<i>-Previously on</i> Marshals...
-[Kayce] <i>I just haven't</i>

2
00:00:05.272 --> 00:00:06.741
<i>seen you in a decade.</i>

3
00:00:06.808 --> 00:00:08.543
You were spinning out
pretty good last time I did.

4
00:00:08.610 --> 00:00:09.844
Get off me.

5
00:00:09.911 --> 00:00:11.078
Hey. You're good.

6
00:00:11.144 --> 00:00:12.881
We both know who
Roner's death is on.

7
00:00:12.947 --> 00:00:14.582
It was my dad's.

8
00:00:14.649 --> 00:00:16.751
<i>I carry it on the off chance</i>
<i>I ever meet his killer.</i>

9
00:00:16.818 --> 00:00:18.352
Family name doesn't
carry water anymore.

10
00:00:18.418 --> 00:00:20.454
so you got to hide
behind a federal badge.

11
00:00:20.522 --> 00:00:22.155
[Calvin]
<i>Deputy Marshal Andrea Cruz</i>

12
00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:23.958
<i>has been abducted.</i>

13
00:00:24.024 --> 00:00:26.861
<i>Let's prep for a full assault</i>
<i>on Randall Clegg's compound.</i>

14
00:00:26.928 --> 00:00:29.329
<i>And with one son dead. another</i>
<i>one facing life in prison.</i>

15
00:00:29.396 --> 00:00:30.732
<i>he's got nothing to lose.</i>

16
00:00:30.798 --> 00:00:32.800
[gunfire]

17
00:00:39.974 --> 00:00:41.074
[gunfire]

18
00:00:41.141 --> 00:00:43.410
♪ intense. dramatic music ♪

19
00:00:49.383 --> 00:00:51.019
We're up against
too much firepower.

20
00:00:51.118 --> 00:00:52.020
We're gonna have to pull back.

21
00:00:52.085 --> 00:00:53.555
Can't leave Andrea behind.

22
00:00:53.621 --> 00:00:55.723
Man. we're no good to her
dead. okay?

23
00:00:55.790 --> 00:00:59.259
Everybody. go back
to the vehicles. Here we go.

24
00:01:02.195 --> 00:01:03.430
Copy that.

25
00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:14.542
[gunfire continues]

26
00:01:33.027 --> 00:01:34.261
Moving.

27
00:01:38.766 --> 00:01:41.168
-Let's go. Come on. let's go!
-Go!

28
00:01:41.970 --> 00:01:45.607
Come on. let's go! Go.

29
00:01:54.782 --> 00:01:56.517
Anybody hit? You good?

30
00:01:56.584 --> 00:01:58.086
Had a whole platoon
hammering us.

31
00:01:58.151 --> 00:01:59.486
How far are we falling back?

32
00:01:59.554 --> 00:02:01.455
Look. head for that
old barn right there.

33
00:02:01.522 --> 00:02:02.757
We got to reload
and hit 'em again.

34
00:02:02.824 --> 00:02:05.093
Okay. none of us
want to leave Andrea.

35
00:02:05.158 --> 00:02:06.193
but this is the best tactic.

36
00:02:06.259 --> 00:02:08.730
Retreating is not a tactic.

37
00:02:15.003 --> 00:02:17.204
♪ soaring. dynamic music ♪

38
00:02:41.829 --> 00:02:43.865
♪♪♪

39
00:02:45.365 --> 00:02:47.602
♪ dramatic music ♪

40
00:02:48.603 --> 00:02:52.874
Okay. We're gonna stronghold
here. figure out our next move.

41
00:02:55.409 --> 00:02:57.011
Cal. you're bleeding.

42
00:02:57.078 --> 00:02:59.113
They move on us. we need to
build up our firing positions.

43
00:02:59.179 --> 00:03:00.515
Let's get eyes up
on that target.

44
00:03:00.581 --> 00:03:02.550
in case they send
anyone else our way.

45
00:03:11.159 --> 00:03:12.794
[grunts softly]

46
00:03:38.351 --> 00:03:40.655
They set up DFPs
all along the perimeter.

47
00:03:41.689 --> 00:03:44.659
See at least ten armed
on that front line.

48
00:03:44.726 --> 00:03:46.293
[Calvin over comms]
<i>Copy that.</i>

49
00:03:47.494 --> 00:03:49.030
Okay. Need a mag check.

50
00:03:49.097 --> 00:03:52.265
-see how much ammo we have left.
-Hold on. you're bleeding.

51
00:03:52.332 --> 00:03:53.901
-Mag check. you heard me.
-[Belle] Cal.

52
00:03:54.736 --> 00:03:58.506
Cal. stop it and put this on.

53
00:03:59.574 --> 00:04:01.642
Okay. can we just.
can we just take a minute

54
00:04:01.709 --> 00:04:03.343
to wrap our heads
around what just happened?

55
00:04:03.410 --> 00:04:05.747
I'm focused
on what happens next.

56
00:04:05.813 --> 00:04:09.550
Stop! We need to understand
the fight we are in

57
00:04:09.617 --> 00:04:12.285
before we start prepping for it.

58
00:04:12.352 --> 00:04:13.755
[sighs]
Okay. look.

59
00:04:13.821 --> 00:04:16.124
we thought we were up against
an angry family

60
00:04:16.190 --> 00:04:18.526
and a few hired guns
that attacked us earlier.

61
00:04:18.593 --> 00:04:21.062
The ambush at the rodeo grounds.
grabbing Andrea.

62
00:04:21.129 --> 00:04:22.797
seems like it was all designed
to lure us here.

63
00:04:22.864 --> 00:04:24.632
Okay. Now we know
what we're up against.

64
00:04:24.699 --> 00:04:26.299
[Belle] Yeah. but what is Andrea
up against in there?

65
00:04:26.366 --> 00:04:27.735
[Miles]
Who are all those fighters?

66
00:04:27.802 --> 00:04:29.336
-Where'd they come from?
-[Belle] Given the four

67
00:04:29.402 --> 00:04:31.038
killed men at the rodeo ambush.

68
00:04:31.105 --> 00:04:34.208
seems Clegg went far and wide
to recruit his crusaders.

69
00:04:34.274 --> 00:04:37.545
I'm-a worry about who they are
after we put 'em down.

70
00:04:37.612 --> 00:04:39.814
[Belle] I'll pass a sitrep
to our Fusion Center.

71
00:04:39.881 --> 00:04:42.116
get FBI and local LEOs
looped in.

72
00:04:42.183 --> 00:04:45.653
but before we attempt another
rescue on Andrea...

73
00:04:45.720 --> 00:04:47.354
We'll need an army of our own.

74
00:04:47.420 --> 00:04:48.388
[Calvin]
Any more questions?

75
00:04:48.455 --> 00:04:51.391
Huh? Or can we do our damn jobs?

76
00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:05.873
Clegg's men are digging in.

77
00:05:05.940 --> 00:05:08.776
No sign they're prepping
for a counterassault.

78
00:05:08.843 --> 00:05:10.912
'Cause Andrea's all he needs.

79
00:05:11.679 --> 00:05:13.714
He has the initiative.

80
00:05:13.781 --> 00:05:17.819
[Kayce] Digging trenches.
assembling firepower.

81
00:05:18.619 --> 00:05:20.288
He's been preparing
for this fight.

82
00:05:20.353 --> 00:05:21.589
[Calvin] Mm-hmm.

83
00:05:21.656 --> 00:05:23.891
Yeah. we just needed
to take the bait.

84
00:05:23.958 --> 00:05:24.992
which I obliged him.

85
00:05:26.761 --> 00:05:29.096
It was the only call to make.

86
00:05:29.163 --> 00:05:31.498
One of ours is in danger. we do
everything we can to save 'em.

87
00:05:31.566 --> 00:05:33.000
It's why we got to roll out
our next wave.

88
00:05:33.067 --> 00:05:35.837
First assault nearly got
our whole team wiped out.

89
00:05:36.971 --> 00:05:40.208
We both know what inaction
leads to in these situations.

90
00:05:40.274 --> 00:05:42.577
Hey. we got to get the ghosts
of Afghanistan out of our heads

91
00:05:42.643 --> 00:05:44.078
if we're gonna get Dre
back safe.

92
00:05:44.145 --> 00:05:46.346
Those aren't the ghosts
that got her into this.

93
00:05:47.315 --> 00:05:48.816
The hell are you talking about?

94
00:05:50.251 --> 00:05:52.352
Dutton curse.

95
00:05:52.419 --> 00:05:54.487
Clegg's had it out
for my family for years.

96
00:05:54.555 --> 00:05:56.389
and I put one of his sons
down hard.

97
00:05:56.456 --> 00:06:00.127
so whatever happens to Andrea.
it's on me.

98
00:06:04.966 --> 00:06:08.435
♪ tense music ♪

99
00:06:08.502 --> 00:06:10.571
[lock clicking]

100
00:06:23.217 --> 00:06:25.620
What's your name? I'm Andrea.

101
00:06:27.387 --> 00:06:29.323
Look. we both heard
that gunfire.

102
00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:31.424
There are people here
to rescue me.

103
00:06:31.491 --> 00:06:33.895
It will be violent.
Okay. you. your baby.

104
00:06:33.961 --> 00:06:35.963
you don't want
to be here for that.

105
00:06:42.303 --> 00:06:43.771
[sighs]

106
00:06:46.641 --> 00:06:48.475
They told me you would lie.

107
00:06:48.542 --> 00:06:52.146
Try to get me
to betray my family.

108
00:06:53.948 --> 00:06:56.918
Now. hold still.
so I can do this.

109
00:07:01.488 --> 00:07:03.791
They want me to blend in
with the women?

110
00:07:05.559 --> 00:07:07.628
Because they're
gonna use the women--

111
00:07:07.695 --> 00:07:09.897
you. your baby--
as their shield.

112
00:07:09.964 --> 00:07:11.933
Listen to me!

113
00:07:11.999 --> 00:07:13.067
[sighs]

114
00:07:14.669 --> 00:07:16.537
Do we have a plan?

115
00:07:16.604 --> 00:07:17.805
Gifford's on his way here.

116
00:07:17.872 --> 00:07:21.108
along with the SAC
from the Bureau.

117
00:07:21.175 --> 00:07:22.510
The FBI's gonna plus us up?

118
00:07:22.576 --> 00:07:24.178
They'll be lead on this.

119
00:07:24.245 --> 00:07:27.447
HRT TAC team's flying in from
Salt Lake City to do the rescue.

120
00:07:27.515 --> 00:07:29.449
We're just gonna
hand over the reins?

121
00:07:29.517 --> 00:07:31.719
It's our teammate in there.
We should be running point.

122
00:07:31.786 --> 00:07:32.853
It's not my call.

123
00:07:32.920 --> 00:07:34.522
We can't just sit and wait.

124
00:07:35.389 --> 00:07:38.392
We need to be coming up with
a plan. even if we don't run it.

125
00:07:38.458 --> 00:07:40.094
Whatever we can do from here.

126
00:07:40.161 --> 00:07:42.964
Let's glass and map the target.
you know? Draw up an infil.

127
00:07:43.030 --> 00:07:45.533
Trying to crack
an impossible infil.

128
00:07:46.801 --> 00:07:48.436
This would be his time to shine.

129
00:07:48.502 --> 00:07:50.404
What the hell
are you talking about?

130
00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:52.673
Garrett.

131
00:07:53.741 --> 00:07:56.010
Airstrip in Ramadi.
prison in J-Bad?

132
00:07:56.077 --> 00:07:58.245
He always found a way
in or around.

133
00:07:58.312 --> 00:08:00.581
Those recon skills would really
help us crack the nut here.

134
00:08:00.648 --> 00:08:01.882
He's a civilian.

135
00:08:01.949 --> 00:08:04.352
So was I till you
stuck a badge on me.

136
00:08:04.418 --> 00:08:05.853
Deputize him.

137
00:08:05.920 --> 00:08:08.155
Double G's way too shaky
to be thrown back into the fire.

138
00:08:08.222 --> 00:08:10.124
Give him a chance to be useful.
You know?

139
00:08:10.191 --> 00:08:12.626
Get back some of the purpose he
lost when you took his Trident.

140
00:08:12.693 --> 00:08:13.995
I don't owe him anything.

141
00:08:14.061 --> 00:08:15.596
I'm not saying we put
a gun in his hand.

142
00:08:15.663 --> 00:08:17.164
but just let him help us
with the X's and O's.

143
00:08:17.231 --> 00:08:18.799
Yeah. and what if he
gets it wrong?

144
00:08:18.866 --> 00:08:20.935
Hmm? You know.
makes a call or. uh.

145
00:08:21.002 --> 00:08:23.170
a mistake we all
got to live with?

146
00:08:23.237 --> 00:08:25.806
All his struggles
happened inside the wire.

147
00:08:25.873 --> 00:08:27.742
But outside.
when was he ever wrong?

148
00:08:30.277 --> 00:08:31.712
[phone buzzing]

149
00:08:31.779 --> 00:08:33.681
You say Clegg is doing this
all because of you?

150
00:08:33.748 --> 00:08:36.417
Then focus on saving Dre.

151
00:08:36.484 --> 00:08:37.718
not Double G.

152
00:08:37.785 --> 00:08:39.854
Yeah. talk to me.

153
00:08:43.024 --> 00:08:44.458
You hear any
of what Cal and Kayce

154
00:08:44.525 --> 00:08:45.760
were talking about down there?

155
00:08:48.596 --> 00:08:50.464
Enough to know that
they're half here

156
00:08:50.531 --> 00:08:53.334
and half in some old war zone.

157
00:08:53.401 --> 00:08:56.103
If those memories are gonna
jeopardize saving Andrea.

158
00:08:56.170 --> 00:08:57.772
we need to squash it.

159
00:08:57.838 --> 00:09:00.474
You and Cal got that whole
work-spouse thing going.

160
00:09:00.541 --> 00:09:01.876
Use it.

161
00:09:02.943 --> 00:09:06.080
Remember that benching we got?

162
00:09:07.481 --> 00:09:09.183
Connection's a bit
frayed lately.

163
00:09:09.250 --> 00:09:10.751
So patch it up.

164
00:09:11.520 --> 00:09:13.554
Andrea's counting on us.

165
00:09:15.856 --> 00:09:18.225
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

166
00:09:20.061 --> 00:09:22.029
[neck cracking]

167
00:09:25.332 --> 00:09:26.567
Hey.

168
00:09:27.536 --> 00:09:30.171
Hey. You still
mapping the target?

169
00:09:30.237 --> 00:09:34.809
Trying to pin down where
everyone's at. including you.

170
00:09:34.875 --> 00:09:37.812
I'm worried your head
has been somewhere else.

171
00:09:37.878 --> 00:09:39.947
My head's focused on saving Dre.

172
00:09:40.014 --> 00:09:41.348
Okay.

173
00:09:43.017 --> 00:09:45.753
Cal. I've never lost a teammate.

174
00:09:45.820 --> 00:09:48.956
And I know you and Kayce have.
more than once.

175
00:09:49.023 --> 00:09:50.458
so maybe that's why
you seem to be

176
00:09:50.525 --> 00:09:52.527
in a different place with this
than Miles and me.

177
00:09:52.593 --> 00:09:55.062
but if we are gonna
bring her home.

178
00:09:55.129 --> 00:09:57.298
the four of us.

179
00:09:57.364 --> 00:09:59.900
we need to be in sync.

180
00:09:59.967 --> 00:10:04.071
Y'all got to see this.
Clegg's livestreaming.

181
00:10:04.138 --> 00:10:08.109
[Randall] <i>...this poison. that</i>
<i>springs from Washington. D.C.</i>

182
00:10:08.175 --> 00:10:10.878
<i>and seeps into every corner</i>
<i>of this once-great land</i>

183
00:10:10.945 --> 00:10:12.947
<i>has tormented me and my family.</i>

184
00:10:13.914 --> 00:10:16.650
<i>Taken my livelihood.</i>

185
00:10:18.886 --> 00:10:21.021
<i>Murdered my son.</i>

186
00:10:22.189 --> 00:10:25.092
<i>Today. federal agents</i>
<i>invaded my land.</i>

187
00:10:25.159 --> 00:10:27.562
<i>I was forced to defend myself.</i>

188
00:10:27.628 --> 00:10:30.664
<i>It is time we take a stand.</i>

189
00:10:33.767 --> 00:10:38.405
<i>With my brave allies by my side.</i>

190
00:10:38.472 --> 00:10:40.975
<i>we will win this war.</i>

191
00:10:41.041 --> 00:10:44.211
♪ dramatic music ♪

192
00:10:50.284 --> 00:10:52.086
So. Special Agent Woods and I
spent the drive

193
00:10:52.153 --> 00:10:55.055
from Helena trying to explain
to D.C. how you let a man

194
00:10:55.122 --> 00:10:57.526
build Montana's
newest military installation

195
00:10:57.592 --> 00:10:59.260
right under your nose.

196
00:10:59.326 --> 00:11:00.794
Okay. well. why-why don't you
ask your G-man here. all right?

197
00:11:00.861 --> 00:11:01.962
Huh? Or ATF?

198
00:11:02.029 --> 00:11:03.030
Right? 'Cause we're the ones

199
00:11:03.097 --> 00:11:04.398
who took Randall Clegg's sons

200
00:11:04.465 --> 00:11:05.499
-off the board.
-Yeah. well.

201
00:11:05.567 --> 00:11:07.067
he's raising his profile today.

202
00:11:07.134 --> 00:11:08.570
Yeah. his stream's gone viral.

203
00:11:08.637 --> 00:11:10.004
Half a million views.
at last count.

204
00:11:10.070 --> 00:11:11.839
[Gifford] Yeah.
man's created a media frenzy

205
00:11:11.906 --> 00:11:13.741
before any news vans
have even arrived on the scene!

206
00:11:13.807 --> 00:11:15.209
[Woods]
Spotlight on this. people start

207
00:11:15.276 --> 00:11:17.912
seeing the next Waco
or Ruby Ridge disaster.

208
00:11:17.978 --> 00:11:19.680
which. in turn. could spark
another Oklahoma City.

209
00:11:19.747 --> 00:11:22.883
Yeah. well. I'm less concerned
about optics than tactics.

210
00:11:22.950 --> 00:11:26.020
like how we're gonna get
Deputy Cruz out of there. stat.

211
00:11:26.086 --> 00:11:27.622
[Woods]
Well. Clegg's not responding to

212
00:11:27.688 --> 00:11:29.056
our negotiator's
attempt to talk.

213
00:11:29.123 --> 00:11:32.193
so all else fails.
TAC team's 90 minutes out.

214
00:11:35.162 --> 00:11:36.363
Double G?

215
00:11:36.430 --> 00:11:38.165
Who the hell's this?

216
00:11:38.232 --> 00:11:41.101
It's a. uh. proven operator
we brought in to consult.

217
00:11:41.168 --> 00:11:43.103
[Gifford] Oh. so you're
bringing in reinforcements

218
00:11:43.170 --> 00:11:44.972
off the streets?

219
00:11:45.039 --> 00:11:47.374
It's all hands on deck.

220
00:11:47.441 --> 00:11:49.343
Even the shaky ones.

221
00:11:49.410 --> 00:11:50.978
I'll get you read in.

222
00:11:51.045 --> 00:11:52.980
♪ tense. dramatic music ♪

223
00:11:57.117 --> 00:11:58.687
Are you a U.S. Marshal

224
00:11:58.786 --> 00:12:01.255
or are you the chairman of
the Frogman Reunion Committee?

225
00:12:01.322 --> 00:12:03.857
[Calvin] Look. Garrett
is just here to help us

226
00:12:03.924 --> 00:12:05.826
prep for a rescue mission

227
00:12:05.893 --> 00:12:08.530
that we'll execute
once the TAC team touches down.

228
00:12:08.597 --> 00:12:10.665
Well. it better be bulletproof

229
00:12:10.731 --> 00:12:12.866
'cause the whole world
is watching.

230
00:12:20.307 --> 00:12:21.775
This is what we got
on the target.

231
00:12:21.842 --> 00:12:24.945
everything we could glass
from here.

232
00:12:25.012 --> 00:12:26.514
Don't have a drone up?

233
00:12:26.581 --> 00:12:27.982
Making do with the bare minimum.

234
00:12:28.048 --> 00:12:29.517
Need you to help turn this
into an infil plan.

235
00:12:29.584 --> 00:12:31.051
Work your old magic.

236
00:12:32.286 --> 00:12:33.588
Hooyah. Coyo.

237
00:12:33.655 --> 00:12:37.124
So you knew Kayce was
bringing in your old teammate?

238
00:12:37.191 --> 00:12:39.661
Need to use all the tools
we have.

239
00:12:39.728 --> 00:12:44.198
[scoffs] Well. realize I'm not a
member of the SEAL brotherhood.

240
00:12:44.265 --> 00:12:48.503
but I may have found a way
to get some intel.

241
00:12:48.570 --> 00:12:52.006
Clegg has a daughter-- Stacy.

242
00:12:52.072 --> 00:12:55.610
Twenty-three. local.
and judging by her socials.

243
00:12:55.677 --> 00:12:57.077
she's cut ties with the family.

244
00:12:57.144 --> 00:13:00.481
Her resentment could be
our greatest resource.

245
00:13:00.548 --> 00:13:01.815
She grew up on the property.

246
00:13:01.882 --> 00:13:03.150
She may know
the lay of the land.

247
00:13:03.217 --> 00:13:05.052
like where her dad
has-has got Dre.

248
00:13:05.119 --> 00:13:08.389
Old wounds can be weaponized.

249
00:13:09.156 --> 00:13:10.924
Okay. make it happen.

250
00:13:14.261 --> 00:13:16.063
I thought I killed this idea?

251
00:13:16.130 --> 00:13:18.032
You saw the message from Clegg.

252
00:13:18.098 --> 00:13:20.502
It's not a negotiation.
We need to find a way inside.

253
00:13:20.568 --> 00:13:23.638
We're working with a massive
blind spot in all this.

254
00:13:23.705 --> 00:13:26.273
There's no intel around the
entire backside of the property.

255
00:13:26.340 --> 00:13:28.309
No idea if he's got guns buried
around the full perimeter.

256
00:13:28.375 --> 00:13:30.344
Or he's got
all his firepower in front.

257
00:13:30.411 --> 00:13:33.080
so he left a weak spot
'round back to exploit.

258
00:13:33.147 --> 00:13:34.616
I smell rabbit holes.

259
00:13:34.683 --> 00:13:38.419
You say this guy Clegg does
rock-blasting for mines?

260
00:13:38.485 --> 00:13:41.121
There's a good chance he dug
some tunnels on his own property

261
00:13:41.188 --> 00:13:42.757
in case of a bugout.

262
00:13:42.823 --> 00:13:44.224
Find one of those.

263
00:13:44.291 --> 00:13:45.660
we could warp zone
straight to his living room.

264
00:13:45.727 --> 00:13:47.461
Team Three pulled
the same thing in Fallujah.

265
00:13:47.529 --> 00:13:49.229
Yeah. remind you.
we are not in Fallujah.

266
00:13:49.296 --> 00:13:50.632
[Kayce]
Garrett and I can do some recon.

267
00:13:50.699 --> 00:13:52.399
get a look.
set up a surveillance camera.

268
00:13:52.466 --> 00:13:54.068
No. you're not stepping foot
near target.

269
00:13:54.134 --> 00:13:56.904
We'll keep our distance.
we'll stay invisible.

270
00:13:56.970 --> 00:13:59.373
I'm good at being a ghost.
eh. Cal?

271
00:14:00.441 --> 00:14:03.477
That's all we need
is another bad war story. Yo.

272
00:14:07.515 --> 00:14:11.085
If there is any hint of contact.
you bail.

273
00:14:11.151 --> 00:14:12.520
♪ tense. suspenseful music ♪

274
00:14:24.666 --> 00:14:27.635
[panting] You're with me. Dad.

275
00:14:27.702 --> 00:14:29.637
telling me not to panic.

276
00:14:35.643 --> 00:14:38.513
No point panicking 'cause
there's always a way to fight.

277
00:14:39.480 --> 00:14:40.948
[grunting]

278
00:14:41.014 --> 00:14:42.116
[crashing]

279
00:14:42.182 --> 00:14:43.585
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

280
00:14:44.686 --> 00:14:45.919
[zip tie snaps]

281
00:14:55.963 --> 00:14:58.198
-This is a blast from the past.
-Huh?

282
00:14:58.265 --> 00:15:00.602
Two of us pulling recon.

283
00:15:00.668 --> 00:15:02.837
Things circle back.

284
00:15:02.903 --> 00:15:04.972
It's more like
a run on repeat for me.

285
00:15:05.939 --> 00:15:09.677
Maybe getting Andrea back's a
shot at atonement for all of us.

286
00:15:11.044 --> 00:15:13.213
Yeah. one thing
the shrinks got right.

287
00:15:13.280 --> 00:15:15.115
I'm better
if I'm looking forward.

288
00:15:17.418 --> 00:15:19.654
[Stacy sighs]
<i>What do you want from me?</i>

289
00:15:19.721 --> 00:15:21.255
I haven't talked
to my old man in years.

290
00:15:21.321 --> 00:15:22.824
I don't know what he's doing.

291
00:15:22.891 --> 00:15:24.592
I understand that. You're
not in any sort of trouble.

292
00:15:24.659 --> 00:15:28.028
But you send cops out
to my work to drag me out here?

293
00:15:28.095 --> 00:15:29.798
We need your help.

294
00:15:29.864 --> 00:15:34.201
Your father. with some people.
took a U.S. Marshal.

295
00:15:35.804 --> 00:15:38.138
I heard on the news.

296
00:15:38.205 --> 00:15:40.407
I don't talk to him.
that's what you're asking for.

297
00:15:40.474 --> 00:15:42.877
No. but you did grow up in
there. and you know the place.

298
00:15:42.943 --> 00:15:44.178
That's why I don't
come out this way.

299
00:15:44.244 --> 00:15:46.581
[breathes sharply]

300
00:15:46.648 --> 00:15:50.350
So. 'less you're gonna charge me
with obstruction or something?

301
00:15:53.487 --> 00:15:55.557
You know the place
I ran from when I was 18?

302
00:15:55.623 --> 00:15:58.358
I wouldn't go within
a hundred miles of it.

303
00:15:58.425 --> 00:16:00.628
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

304
00:16:00.695 --> 00:16:02.396
You're braver than me.

305
00:16:08.202 --> 00:16:09.403
Different type of house.

306
00:16:09.470 --> 00:16:12.306
different type
of haunting. maybe.

307
00:16:13.106 --> 00:16:15.777
But I know what
it must've taken for you

308
00:16:15.844 --> 00:16:19.781
to claw your way out of there.

309
00:16:19.848 --> 00:16:22.617
Help my friend do the same.

310
00:16:22.684 --> 00:16:24.719
[door creaking]

311
00:16:30.424 --> 00:16:31.992
[screams]

312
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:34.194
[knife clatters]

313
00:16:35.496 --> 00:16:36.764
[choking]

314
00:16:50.444 --> 00:16:52.780
[whispers]
What are their numbers?

315
00:16:54.047 --> 00:16:56.483
[phone beeping]

316
00:16:56.551 --> 00:16:58.385
Oh. come on.

317
00:17:14.101 --> 00:17:15.637
Kayce. you have about 20 meters

318
00:17:15.703 --> 00:17:17.739
<i>before you're out</i>
<i>of my line of sight.</i>

319
00:17:21.809 --> 00:17:24.044
Copy that. We'll push on.

320
00:17:27.849 --> 00:17:29.617
Makes sense you'd want Garrett.

321
00:17:30.785 --> 00:17:32.854
War's got to forge a trust
that's hard to find

322
00:17:32.921 --> 00:17:34.087
with anyone else.

323
00:17:34.154 --> 00:17:35.757
Trust isn't permanent.

324
00:17:36.624 --> 00:17:38.058
Told you. I didn't
know Maddie was--

325
00:17:38.125 --> 00:17:39.627
Yeah. we're not talking
about that here.

326
00:17:42.162 --> 00:17:43.965
No dug-in
firing positions back here.

327
00:17:44.032 --> 00:17:45.432
just a couple guys on foot.

328
00:17:45.499 --> 00:17:48.770
[Garrett] Everything
we dreamed it would be.

329
00:17:48.836 --> 00:17:52.674
Forget tunnels. infil
on this side will be easy day.

330
00:17:52.740 --> 00:17:55.944
Let's get closer. rig a cam.
so we can keep eyes on.

331
00:17:56.010 --> 00:17:58.245
♪♪♪

332
00:18:00.949 --> 00:18:03.383
[panting]

333
00:18:06.186 --> 00:18:07.487
[line rings]

334
00:18:07.555 --> 00:18:08.790
[operator]
<i>911. What's your emergency?</i>

335
00:18:08.856 --> 00:18:11.593
This is Deputy
U.S. Marshal Andrea Cruz.

336
00:18:11.659 --> 00:18:13.427
I can't talk. but just
stay on the line. listen.

337
00:18:13.493 --> 00:18:15.262
and don't say a word.

338
00:18:22.169 --> 00:18:24.404
♪ exciting. dramatic music ♪

339
00:18:38.086 --> 00:18:40.320
♪♪♪

340
00:18:53.568 --> 00:18:54.802
[gasps]

341
00:18:57.639 --> 00:18:59.807
Somebody's coming out
of that main house.

342
00:19:11.919 --> 00:19:14.187
Okay. Kayce. you have
two armed suspects

343
00:19:14.254 --> 00:19:15.690
patrolling your way.

344
00:19:15.757 --> 00:19:19.326
Do you copy? You have two
incoming from the south.

345
00:19:23.665 --> 00:19:25.800
♪ intense. dramatic music ♪

346
00:19:30.237 --> 00:19:31.773
You had any range time?

347
00:19:31.839 --> 00:19:35.043
It's not exactly
a perk of psych wards.

348
00:19:35.843 --> 00:19:38.345
Never really leaves you.
though. does it?

349
00:19:42.116 --> 00:19:43.483
No. it does not.

350
00:19:48.623 --> 00:19:50.058
[Kayce]
Cal. they're still incoming.

351
00:19:50.124 --> 00:19:51.425
<i>Need some help here.</i>

352
00:19:51.491 --> 00:19:52.960
I knew I shouldn't have let them
out of my sight.

353
00:19:53.027 --> 00:19:55.163
♪ tense. suspenseful music ♪

354
00:19:55.228 --> 00:19:56.764
Don't got to see 'em
to help 'em.

355
00:20:00.835 --> 00:20:01.903
[distant gunfire]

356
00:20:06.140 --> 00:20:07.108
[Calvin]
You're clear.

357
00:20:07.175 --> 00:20:08.910
We're RTB.

358
00:20:10.310 --> 00:20:14.882
That diversion tactic
just saved their asses.

359
00:20:14.949 --> 00:20:16.617
Think you can trust me now?

360
00:20:21.421 --> 00:20:23.057
Just stay on overwatch.

361
00:20:23.124 --> 00:20:25.626
♪♪♪

362
00:20:29.630 --> 00:20:31.264
[Belle]
All right. we've got audio.

363
00:20:31.331 --> 00:20:32.900
We're patched into the call.

364
00:20:32.967 --> 00:20:34.635
Audio of what?

365
00:20:34.702 --> 00:20:37.270
Uh. Deputy Marshal Cruz somehow
found a phone and called 911.

366
00:20:37.337 --> 00:20:39.874
Haven't heard her voice yet.
but the line is still open.

367
00:20:39.941 --> 00:20:41.441
Ping it to her location?

368
00:20:41.509 --> 00:20:42.977
[sighs] It's hard to
narrow it down in the compound.

369
00:20:43.044 --> 00:20:45.245
Okay. well.
we're in their playbook now.

370
00:20:45.312 --> 00:20:46.814
so I need a sitrep
on everything we got.

371
00:20:46.881 --> 00:20:50.118
Well. Stacy ID'd the backdrop
of her dad's video

372
00:20:50.184 --> 00:20:52.620
as the basement
in the main house.

373
00:20:52.687 --> 00:20:54.454
Other than that.
said the man is sadistic.

374
00:20:54.522 --> 00:20:56.423
Used to punish her amongst

375
00:20:56.490 --> 00:20:59.127
the rotted animals
in the tanning shed.

376
00:20:59.193 --> 00:21:00.595
Hey.

377
00:21:01.529 --> 00:21:02.697
Your trek good for anything more

378
00:21:02.764 --> 00:21:04.431
than stripping ten years
off my life?

379
00:21:04.498 --> 00:21:06.834
Backside of the property's
a soft target.

380
00:21:06.901 --> 00:21:08.268
just a few roaming guns.

381
00:21:08.335 --> 00:21:09.570
We set a cam to surveil.

382
00:21:09.637 --> 00:21:11.539
Okay. No sign of Dre?

383
00:21:11.606 --> 00:21:13.273
No.

384
00:21:19.312 --> 00:21:21.348
-Hey.
-Hey.

385
00:21:21.414 --> 00:21:23.283
Why don't you take a break
for a minute.

386
00:21:23.350 --> 00:21:25.920
Get some fresh air.
I'll listen for Andrea.

387
00:21:25.987 --> 00:21:27.320
I'm good.

388
00:21:28.923 --> 00:21:30.625
Still gonna tell me
whatever's going on

389
00:21:30.691 --> 00:21:32.459
with that neck is nothing?

390
00:21:35.663 --> 00:21:38.032
Forget about
the work boundaries.

391
00:21:38.099 --> 00:21:40.835
What is going on?

392
00:21:44.539 --> 00:21:46.207
You were right earlier.

393
00:21:46.274 --> 00:21:48.042
Yeah. my head has been
somewhere else.

394
00:21:48.109 --> 00:21:49.877
and so has Kayce's.

395
00:21:51.045 --> 00:21:53.480
We're just both
trying to fix history

396
00:21:53.548 --> 00:21:55.315
we're afraid of repeating.

397
00:21:57.752 --> 00:22:00.353
History that happened
with Garrett?

398
00:22:01.488 --> 00:22:03.390
[Randall over phone] <i>Thought</i>
<i>you'd slither out of here?</i>

399
00:22:03.456 --> 00:22:05.893
♪ suspenseful music ♪

400
00:22:08.796 --> 00:22:11.364
Stabbing one of my guys
in the back.

401
00:22:13.801 --> 00:22:15.570
See you fight like a Dutton.

402
00:22:15.636 --> 00:22:18.773
Just trying to get a better view
of your lovely home.

403
00:22:18.840 --> 00:22:20.708
Yellow accent wall's
a nice touch.

404
00:22:20.775 --> 00:22:22.076
Is that a spruce outside?

405
00:22:23.945 --> 00:22:27.014
<i>-Beautiful tree.</i>
-She's feeding us her location.

406
00:22:28.381 --> 00:22:31.484
Tongue is almost
as sharp as this.

407
00:22:33.120 --> 00:22:36.557
What do you want
from all this? Money?

408
00:22:36.624 --> 00:22:38.425
I work for my money.

409
00:22:38.491 --> 00:22:40.294
Or I used to. at least.

410
00:22:40.360 --> 00:22:43.030
before the government
turned their back on those who

411
00:22:43.097 --> 00:22:46.000
dirtied their hands
building this country.

412
00:22:47.001 --> 00:22:50.905
Attention. then?
I'm sure you've got it now.

413
00:22:50.972 --> 00:22:53.808
<i>People hear your story.</i>
<i>they'll feel for you.</i>

414
00:22:53.875 --> 00:22:56.177
<i>Losing one son.</i>
<i>another locked up.</i>

415
00:22:56.244 --> 00:22:58.079
They'll get why you're angry.

416
00:22:58.145 --> 00:23:00.248
And when you let me walk
out of here. you'll be a hero.

417
00:23:00.314 --> 00:23:01.515
[Randall]
You got as much chance

418
00:23:01.582 --> 00:23:04.252
of walking out of here
as my son--

419
00:23:04.318 --> 00:23:07.688
who Kayce Dutton murdered--
has of walking back in.

420
00:23:07.755 --> 00:23:09.389
He wasn't murdered.

421
00:23:09.456 --> 00:23:11.225
He shot innocent people.

422
00:23:11.292 --> 00:23:13.628
Made a bad choice.

423
00:23:13.694 --> 00:23:15.029
You can make a good one.

424
00:23:15.096 --> 00:23:16.631
I already made my choice.

425
00:23:16.697 --> 00:23:19.767
The government stopped
standing up for the people.

426
00:23:20.902 --> 00:23:22.670
Let me demonstrate to you
what happens

427
00:23:22.737 --> 00:23:25.039
when people
stop fighting for me.

428
00:23:25.106 --> 00:23:27.074
No. no. Randall!

429
00:23:28.342 --> 00:23:30.011
[Randall]
You got one thing right.

430
00:23:30.077 --> 00:23:32.613
My fight.

431
00:23:32.680 --> 00:23:35.583
it's getting
the attention it warrants.

432
00:23:36.350 --> 00:23:37.852
And soon.

433
00:23:37.919 --> 00:23:41.956
you will help me
remind my audience

434
00:23:42.023 --> 00:23:46.426
that revolution
is a struggle to the death.

435
00:23:49.263 --> 00:23:50.965
Shut her up.

436
00:23:53.901 --> 00:23:55.536
[Belle]
<i>He just killed one of his own.</i>

437
00:23:55.603 --> 00:23:57.838
There is no way
he's gonna let Andrea survive.

438
00:23:57.905 --> 00:23:58.673
We need to move.

439
00:23:58.739 --> 00:24:00.608
TAC team's still 40 minutes out.

440
00:24:00.675 --> 00:24:01.909
Then we got to go without 'em.

441
00:24:07.949 --> 00:24:09.317
All right. Stacy Clegg
confirmed that there is a den

442
00:24:09.383 --> 00:24:11.852
on the first floor of the house.
northwest corner.

443
00:24:11.919 --> 00:24:13.721
with a yellow wall
and a spruce outside.

444
00:24:13.788 --> 00:24:15.589
Andrea's last known 20.

445
00:24:15.656 --> 00:24:17.825
Cam's still showing
weak security in the back.

446
00:24:17.892 --> 00:24:19.560
Then that's where we'll breach.

447
00:24:19.627 --> 00:24:21.195
[Gifford]
<i>People may be getting riled up</i>

448
00:24:21.262 --> 00:24:22.763
<i>about this livestream.</i>

449
00:24:22.830 --> 00:24:24.497
but we have no evidence
that escalation is imminent.

450
00:24:24.565 --> 00:24:28.102
He just threatened to kill Dre
to start his own revolution.

451
00:24:28.169 --> 00:24:31.172
The head shed in D.C. is
all over my ass to deconflict.

452
00:24:31.238 --> 00:24:35.109
Deconflict? Harry. Clegg is in
this too deep to back down now.

453
00:24:35.176 --> 00:24:38.746
[sighs] We need
to consider the optics.

454
00:24:38.813 --> 00:24:40.815
Dre is in the crosshairs.

455
00:24:40.881 --> 00:24:42.183
and you're thinking
about headlines?

456
00:24:42.249 --> 00:24:43.751
Headlines?

457
00:24:43.818 --> 00:24:45.987
The president is holed up
in his residence

458
00:24:46.053 --> 00:24:48.322
watching this madman
in real time.

459
00:24:48.389 --> 00:24:49.623
There's time to negotiate.

460
00:24:49.690 --> 00:24:50.858
We still don't know
what Clegg wants.

461
00:24:50.925 --> 00:24:52.893
This is what he wants.
This. okay?

462
00:24:52.960 --> 00:24:55.997
A platform to deliver his own
brand of frontier justice

463
00:24:56.063 --> 00:24:58.099
by publicly executing
a U.S. Marshal.

464
00:24:58.165 --> 00:25:01.268
If you act unilaterally.
you own this entire mess.

465
00:25:01.335 --> 00:25:04.305
I will turn that chopper around.
and I was never here.

466
00:25:04.372 --> 00:25:08.542
Oh. how is that for "Fidelity.
Bravery. and Integrity."

467
00:25:08.609 --> 00:25:10.845
That is my marshal in there.

468
00:25:10.911 --> 00:25:12.380
Hey. you want to hit the road
with her. hmm?

469
00:25:12.446 --> 00:25:15.750
Get your distance? Be my guest.
Now's your chance.

470
00:25:15.816 --> 00:25:18.219
♪ tense. dramatic music ♪

471
00:25:18.285 --> 00:25:21.889
Rifle. scope.
I'll cover your insolent asses.

472
00:25:22.823 --> 00:25:24.191
[Calvin]
Rifle's upstairs.

473
00:25:24.258 --> 00:25:26.160
And remember. boss.
shoot out the barrel end.

474
00:25:26.227 --> 00:25:28.362
Yeah. Just get Cruz back.

475
00:25:28.429 --> 00:25:31.298
I may not like her wobbling jaw.

476
00:25:31.365 --> 00:25:33.601
but she's the best of us.

477
00:25:38.439 --> 00:25:41.642
[Calvin] Okay. so Gifford's
on overwatch. Let's roll.

478
00:25:41.709 --> 00:25:44.578
You know.
four against 20's no joke.

479
00:25:44.645 --> 00:25:46.647
One more rifle couldn't hurt.

480
00:25:50.051 --> 00:25:51.952
That is not what he is here for.

481
00:25:53.254 --> 00:25:55.489
We're reunited.
got a teammate in need.

482
00:25:55.556 --> 00:25:57.024
It feels like
he's here for a reason.

483
00:25:57.091 --> 00:25:59.226
Team's only as strong
as its weakest member. Coyo.

484
00:25:59.293 --> 00:26:01.595
and we both know Double G's
carrying a lot more

485
00:26:01.662 --> 00:26:02.863
than a rifle downrange.

486
00:26:02.930 --> 00:26:05.833
Andrea's life's on the line.

487
00:26:05.900 --> 00:26:08.936
You sure you're comfortable
leaving a round in the chamber?

488
00:26:12.273 --> 00:26:14.975
[speaking indistinctly]

489
00:26:19.880 --> 00:26:22.116
♪ suspenseful. dramatic music ♪

490
00:26:33.160 --> 00:26:34.361
You good?

491
00:26:38.466 --> 00:26:40.167
What's the holdup. Coyo?

492
00:26:41.368 --> 00:26:43.904
I don't trust Gifford
on overwatch.

493
00:26:43.971 --> 00:26:45.940
I need you to have our backs
when we're out there.

494
00:26:46.740 --> 00:26:48.008
I got your six down here.

495
00:26:52.079 --> 00:26:54.081
Need you to RTB.

496
00:27:03.491 --> 00:27:05.126
You made the right call.

497
00:27:31.318 --> 00:27:34.722
[speaking indistinctly]

498
00:27:35.890 --> 00:27:38.159
We're outnumbered before
we even get to the door.

499
00:27:38.225 --> 00:27:39.760
Wait 'em out?
See if they move off?

500
00:27:39.827 --> 00:27:41.795
[Belle]
She can't afford us waiting.

501
00:27:44.965 --> 00:27:47.368
Hold here.
I'll go turn some heads.

502
00:27:48.736 --> 00:27:50.804
♪♪♪

503
00:28:17.498 --> 00:28:20.167
Cal. move to the house
when this thing blows.

504
00:28:20.234 --> 00:28:22.136
I'll catch up.

505
00:28:32.346 --> 00:28:33.981
[grunting]

506
00:28:38.919 --> 00:28:41.155
[straining. choking]

507
00:28:44.693 --> 00:28:48.996
[shouting indistinctly]

508
00:29:02.910 --> 00:29:04.478
We need to breach.

509
00:29:08.148 --> 00:29:10.784
♪ tense. suspenseful music ♪

510
00:29:16.323 --> 00:29:17.692
[knife clatters]

511
00:29:17.758 --> 00:29:19.426
[gunshots]

512
00:29:19.493 --> 00:29:20.528
Belle. take point.

513
00:29:21.762 --> 00:29:24.031
[both grunting]

514
00:29:29.036 --> 00:29:31.038
[Andrea grunting]

515
00:29:40.682 --> 00:29:41.915
Come here. [grunts]

516
00:29:49.089 --> 00:29:50.257
Cal. I'm moving on your pos.

517
00:29:50.324 --> 00:29:52.026
[Garrett]
<i>Coyo. this is Knife.</i>

518
00:29:52.092 --> 00:29:53.127
<i>I got two suspects</i>
<i>between you and your target.</i>

519
00:29:53.193 --> 00:29:54.862
<i>Hook wide right and around.</i>

520
00:29:54.928 --> 00:29:56.897
♪ tense. suspenseful music ♪

521
00:29:58.667 --> 00:30:00.067
Copy.

522
00:30:27.161 --> 00:30:28.530
-[gunshot]
-[grunts]

523
00:30:30.998 --> 00:30:32.299
[gunfire]

524
00:30:47.014 --> 00:30:49.450
[both grunting]

525
00:30:55.623 --> 00:30:57.858
♪♪♪

526
00:31:02.630 --> 00:31:04.331
[Miles]
All right. hold.

527
00:31:06.768 --> 00:31:08.202
[grunts]

528
00:31:17.812 --> 00:31:19.179
[grunts]

529
00:31:20.147 --> 00:31:22.817
You ain't getting off that easy.

530
00:31:22.883 --> 00:31:24.485
Clear that weapon.

531
00:31:25.486 --> 00:31:26.920
Come on.

532
00:31:26.987 --> 00:31:28.422
Let's go.

533
00:31:28.489 --> 00:31:30.759
[man over radio]
<i>Sovereign. what's your sitrep?</i>

534
00:31:30.825 --> 00:31:31.959
House is clear.

535
00:31:32.025 --> 00:31:33.394
-[handcuffs clicking]
-[groans]

536
00:31:34.629 --> 00:31:36.163
[Calvin]
Okay.

537
00:31:36.230 --> 00:31:38.899
Now. you tell your men
to drop their weapons. Come on.

538
00:31:38.966 --> 00:31:40.200
Come on. come on.
You don't want 'em

539
00:31:40.267 --> 00:31:42.269
bogarting your martyrdom.
do you? Huh?

540
00:31:42.336 --> 00:31:45.840
[panting] This is Sovereign.

541
00:31:45.906 --> 00:31:47.941
All stand down.

542
00:31:48.810 --> 00:31:51.111
-Okay. Get him up.
-[grunts]

543
00:31:52.781 --> 00:31:54.649
I got you.

544
00:31:56.751 --> 00:31:58.986
Kayce. where are the others?
Are they okay?

545
00:31:59.052 --> 00:32:01.321
[Kayce]
Yeah. they're good.

546
00:32:06.093 --> 00:32:09.029
One Hotel Lima. She's with me.

547
00:32:09.096 --> 00:32:11.031
[Calvin]
<i>Hooyah. Roger that.</i>

548
00:32:14.869 --> 00:32:16.236
[grunts]

549
00:32:22.443 --> 00:32:24.211
-Let's get you home.
-[sighs]

550
00:32:24.278 --> 00:32:26.514
That's a long way from here.

551
00:32:31.285 --> 00:32:33.454
♪ quiet. dramatic music ♪

552
00:32:43.765 --> 00:32:46.668
You know. a real man
would've come for me directly.

553
00:32:46.734 --> 00:32:48.603
I don't take lectures on manhood

554
00:32:48.670 --> 00:32:52.607
from a family that thinks power
comes from land and badges.

555
00:32:54.274 --> 00:32:57.144
I really wish my father
was still around.

556
00:32:57.211 --> 00:33:00.047
so he could see Montana
rid itself of the Cleggs.

557
00:33:02.917 --> 00:33:06.386
You may have wiped out my kin.

558
00:33:06.453 --> 00:33:11.191
but my family tree
has blossomed today.

559
00:33:11.258 --> 00:33:14.562
And unlike the Duttons.

560
00:33:14.629 --> 00:33:16.463
my legacy is growing.

561
00:33:16.531 --> 00:33:18.733
[Calvin]
Okay. bud. Come on.

562
00:33:23.638 --> 00:33:25.673
♪♪♪

563
00:33:28.008 --> 00:33:29.443
[indistinct chatter]

564
00:33:31.111 --> 00:33:33.447
[indistinct radio chatter]

565
00:33:33.515 --> 00:33:36.116
[quiet chatter]

566
00:33:36.183 --> 00:33:37.619
[Calvin]
Hey.

567
00:33:40.053 --> 00:33:41.723
I shouldn't have left you alone.

568
00:33:41.789 --> 00:33:43.825
For a delivery?

569
00:33:43.892 --> 00:33:46.159
Let yourself off the hook. boss.

570
00:33:47.227 --> 00:33:50.297
Thank you. for fighting for me.

571
00:33:56.303 --> 00:33:59.507
[vehicle doors opening. closing]

572
00:33:59.574 --> 00:34:01.609
[engine starts]

573
00:34:03.377 --> 00:34:05.178
I'm not officially
part of the team.

574
00:34:05.245 --> 00:34:07.147
so you can't kick me off it.

575
00:34:09.751 --> 00:34:12.119
Look. you helped us avoid
the worst today.

576
00:34:12.887 --> 00:34:14.187
Thank you.

577
00:34:19.159 --> 00:34:21.461
Roner still haunts me. too.

578
00:34:22.296 --> 00:34:23.998
And as messed up as that was.

579
00:34:24.064 --> 00:34:26.233
you know. it's sometimes
easier to accept

580
00:34:26.300 --> 00:34:29.202
than what went down between us.

581
00:34:32.941 --> 00:34:35.442
I know what you mean. boss.

582
00:34:46.286 --> 00:34:47.755
[softly] Okay.

583
00:34:55.362 --> 00:34:58.298
Thank you. Stacy.

584
00:34:59.499 --> 00:35:01.468
Is there anything you need?

585
00:35:02.336 --> 00:35:04.237
New last name?

586
00:35:05.372 --> 00:35:09.476
Clegg'll be an even dirtier word
than it was before.

587
00:35:11.813 --> 00:35:13.380
Leave here.

588
00:35:14.649 --> 00:35:18.352
Get so far away
that none of it-- the name.

589
00:35:18.418 --> 00:35:22.890
the things they've done--
can find you.

590
00:35:24.559 --> 00:35:28.730
Make a life for yourself.
instead of against all this.

591
00:35:30.999 --> 00:35:32.432
Thank you.

592
00:35:33.467 --> 00:35:37.137
Let's get you out of here.
Miles.

593
00:35:38.906 --> 00:35:40.908
Let's take her to the car.

594
00:35:40.975 --> 00:35:42.376
[Gifford]
Nerve of you.

595
00:35:43.176 --> 00:35:45.580
Served you well today.

596
00:35:45.647 --> 00:35:50.217
Suppose what I mistook in you
as recklessness

597
00:35:50.283 --> 00:35:52.185
may be fearlessness.

598
00:35:53.021 --> 00:35:54.689
Not a bad trait in a lawman.

599
00:35:54.756 --> 00:35:56.289
with the right guidance.

600
00:35:58.325 --> 00:36:00.528
That's called an olive branch.

601
00:36:00.595 --> 00:36:03.798
I realize that's a rare sight
on Dutton land.

602
00:36:03.865 --> 00:36:05.933
About as rare as caring
what people think about us.

603
00:36:06.000 --> 00:36:07.568
[sighs]

604
00:36:09.003 --> 00:36:11.171
You had our backs today.

605
00:36:12.774 --> 00:36:14.441
That mattered.

606
00:36:26.721 --> 00:36:29.524
Guess you had somebody
helping you out in there.

607
00:36:35.228 --> 00:36:37.965
[sighs] We made it. Dad.

608
00:36:44.371 --> 00:36:45.873
[Belle]
<i>Wow.</i>

609
00:36:45.940 --> 00:36:49.443
Who knew the Lone Ranger
had such a knack for hosting.

610
00:36:49.510 --> 00:36:51.145
Charcuterie and everything.

611
00:36:51.211 --> 00:36:53.781
That's the
special occasion jerky.

612
00:37:01.856 --> 00:37:04.092
Monica put those up.

613
00:37:04.158 --> 00:37:05.660
She was proud.

614
00:37:06.460 --> 00:37:08.629
You ever tell her about it?

615
00:37:09.597 --> 00:37:10.998
I mean. about all of it?

616
00:37:11.933 --> 00:37:15.235
No. I didn't want to
fill her head with that stuff.

617
00:37:17.337 --> 00:37:19.473
Yeah. wish we had that option.

618
00:37:22.510 --> 00:37:24.846
Sorry for how it went
for you out there.

619
00:37:25.680 --> 00:37:28.182
Getting pulled from the action.

620
00:37:28.248 --> 00:37:29.416
I'm not.

621
00:37:29.483 --> 00:37:31.418
I don't miss it.

622
00:37:32.520 --> 00:37:35.556
I still get plenty to wake up
screaming at night.

623
00:37:36.891 --> 00:37:39.193
What I miss
is what you got here.

624
00:37:39.259 --> 00:37:42.797
room full of teammates that'd
do anything for each other.

625
00:37:44.165 --> 00:37:45.166
Well. you got me. brother.

626
00:37:46.033 --> 00:37:47.769
That's why
I ain't leaving. brother.

627
00:37:47.835 --> 00:37:49.637
♪ gentle music ♪

628
00:37:52.573 --> 00:37:54.307
[Andrea] Hey. Double G.
is this venue big enough

629
00:37:54.374 --> 00:37:55.810
for you to play for me?

630
00:37:55.877 --> 00:37:58.179
No. I'm not the star
of the show tonight. That's you.

631
00:37:58.246 --> 00:38:01.314
[chuckles] Really? You're
gonna say no to your muse?

632
00:38:01.381 --> 00:38:03.217
Ah. come on. Double G.

633
00:38:03.283 --> 00:38:04.685
[Andrea laughs]

634
00:38:04.752 --> 00:38:06.954
Woman just went toe-to-toe
with Randall Clegg.

635
00:38:07.021 --> 00:38:08.823
Really think she's gonna
back down from you?

636
00:38:09.924 --> 00:38:12.693
I guess who am I to say no
to the lady of the hour?

637
00:38:12.760 --> 00:38:16.329
But I do sound a whole lot
better out under the stars.

638
00:38:21.002 --> 00:38:22.503
[Belle]
How's that neck?

639
00:38:22.570 --> 00:38:24.539
I'm fine. I told you.

640
00:38:24.605 --> 00:38:27.008
Yeah? Then what happened
back at the op?

641
00:38:27.074 --> 00:38:30.711
I just. I tweaked it
when we first took contact.

642
00:38:33.014 --> 00:38:35.016
Whatever's going on...

643
00:38:36.551 --> 00:38:38.351
...you can talk to me.

644
00:38:39.520 --> 00:38:41.889
Well. let's just enjoy
the victory.

645
00:38:41.956 --> 00:38:44.424
[guitar playing]

646
00:38:54.401 --> 00:38:56.204
♪ <i>If I had it my way</i> ♪

647
00:38:56.270 --> 00:39:00.440
♪ <i>I'd be watching your eyes turn</i>
<i>from brown to hazel right now</i> ♪

648
00:39:02.009 --> 00:39:04.444
♪ <i>Way they did</i>
<i>on the front porch swing</i> ♪

649
00:39:04.512 --> 00:39:06.214
♪ <i>When the sky turned red</i> ♪

650
00:39:06.280 --> 00:39:08.316
♪ <i>Watching the sun go down</i> ♪

651
00:39:08.381 --> 00:39:10.952
♪ <i>Be a field full of fireflies</i> ♪

652
00:39:11.018 --> 00:39:13.921
♪ <i>Watching this lost time</i>
<i>making up</i> ♪

653
00:39:15.223 --> 00:39:19.392
♪ <i>You'd be in my arms.</i>
<i>we'd still be in love</i> ♪

654
00:39:20.895 --> 00:39:23.531
♪ <i>If I had it my way</i> ♪

655
00:39:26.934 --> 00:39:29.704
♪ <i>If I had it my way</i> ♪

656
00:39:33.941 --> 00:39:36.077
♪ <i>If I had it my way</i> ♪

657
00:39:36.143 --> 00:39:40.748
♪ <i>I would blink and we'd</i>
<i>disappear somewhere somehow</i> ♪

658
00:39:41.883 --> 00:39:44.218
♪ <i>Have a little bit</i>
<i>of red wine poured</i> ♪

659
00:39:44.285 --> 00:39:48.022
♪ <i>Into coffee cups</i>
<i>watching the stars come out</i> ♪

660
00:39:48.089 --> 00:39:50.691
♪ <i>We'd have</i>
<i>an Al Green record on</i> ♪

661
00:39:50.758 --> 00:39:53.527
♪ <i>Dance a little</i>
<i>by the fireplace</i> ♪

662
00:39:54.762 --> 00:39:58.465
♪ <i>We'd make our love.</i>
<i>and we'd just lay</i> ♪

663
00:39:59.934 --> 00:40:02.737
♪ <i>If I had it my way</i> ♪

664
00:40:06.040 --> 00:40:07.942
♪ "My Way"
by Riley Green playing ♪

665
00:40:08.009 --> 00:40:11.045
♪ <i>Call me up and say</i>
<i>I need you now</i> ♪

666
00:40:11.112 --> 00:40:13.781
♪ <i>And I can't go another day</i> ♪

667
00:40:15.049 --> 00:40:17.652
♪ <i>Say you're all</i>
<i>I ever think about</i> ♪

668
00:40:17.718 --> 00:40:20.888
♪ <i>Now. I'd give anything</i>
<i>to see your face</i> ♪

669
00:40:22.290 --> 00:40:24.258
♪ <i>You'd say I miss you</i> ♪

670
00:40:24.325 --> 00:40:29.931
♪ <i>I'd say I don't know</i>
<i>how much more I can take</i> ♪

671
00:40:30.798 --> 00:40:32.233
♪ <i>You'd say I'm on my way</i> ♪

672
00:40:32.300 --> 00:40:33.634
Do you want to be alone?

673
00:40:34.902 --> 00:40:36.037
♪ <i>If I had it my way</i> ♪

674
00:40:36.103 --> 00:40:37.505
No.

675
00:40:38.539 --> 00:40:39.874
You?

676
00:40:46.514 --> 00:40:48.149
Can I ask you something?

677
00:40:49.050 --> 00:40:50.450
♪ <i>If I had it my way...</i> ♪

678
00:40:50.518 --> 00:40:53.087
When you were in that house.

679
00:40:53.154 --> 00:40:55.957
did you make it to the door?
Get it open?

680
00:40:57.158 --> 00:40:58.693
You saw me?

681
00:40:59.492 --> 00:41:01.395
No. but I had a feeling.

682
00:41:01.461 --> 00:41:04.031
♪ <i>On the living room couch</i> ♪

683
00:41:04.098 --> 00:41:05.498
♪ <i>Have a John Wayne western on</i> ♪

684
00:41:05.566 --> 00:41:07.435
Cowboy getting all cosmic on me.

685
00:41:07.500 --> 00:41:10.204
♪ <i>That we weren't</i>
<i>watching anyway</i> ♪

686
00:41:11.539 --> 00:41:12.840
♪ <i>Girl. I swear I would...</i> ♪

687
00:41:12.907 --> 00:41:15.109
Bet you don't have stars
like this back east.

688
00:41:16.510 --> 00:41:18.212
No.

689
00:41:18.279 --> 00:41:21.782
Also don't have people
kidnapping me back east.

690
00:41:23.117 --> 00:41:24.452
Fair.

691
00:41:24.518 --> 00:41:27.021
♪ <i>If I had it my way</i> ♪

692
00:41:27.989 --> 00:41:31.125
Jury's still out
on this place. but...

693
00:41:31.192 --> 00:41:34.494
as long as I'm here. I'm glad
it's on a team with you.

694
00:41:38.432 --> 00:41:40.568
♪ <i>If I had it my way</i> ♪

695
00:41:40.634 --> 00:41:45.940
♪ <i>I would just lean in</i>
<i>and kiss your lips right now</i> ♪

696
00:41:50.044 --> 00:41:52.279
♪ intense. percussive music ♪
